# Git Workflow & Governance

## Conventional Commits (Required)

```
feat:     New feature (MINOR version bump)
fix:      Bug fix (PATCH version bump)
refactor: Code restructuring (no behavior change)
docs:     Documentation changes
chore:    Build, tooling, dependencies
test:     Test additions/modifications
perf:     Performance improvement
security: Security fix (triggers Gate 3 review)
clinical: Clinical logic change (triggers Gate 5 + Gate 6 review)
```

Format: `<type>(scope): <description under 60 chars>`
Example: `feat(cdss): add qSOFA sepsis scoring engine`

## Branch Strategy

- `main` → protected, requires PR + Guardian GREEN
- `feat/*` → feature branches
- `fix/*` → bug fix branches
- `clinical/*` → clinical logic changes (require Chief review)

## Pre-Commit Checks (via Husky)

1. `pnpm typecheck` — TypeScript strict
2. `pnpm lint` — ESLint zero warnings
3. `pnpm test --changed` — tests for changed files only

## Critical: Clinical Logic Changes

Any commit touching `src/lib/cdss/` MUST:
- Use `clinical:` commit type
- Include test coverage proof
- Be flagged for Gate 5 (Chief approval) and Gate 6 (Agent eval)
